Shamith Maharaj is the Executive of Data Networks at BCX. Maharaj is a self-motivated individual who has 18 years of global telecommunications experience. This experience spans fields like project management, network design, network activations, network operations, network management, IT management, and service assurance. One of the hallmarks of Maharaj’s career has been building strong relationships with customers and suppliers. This has helped him to improve the overall customer experience wherever he has worked. In this episode of Business Talk, Maharaj discusses autonomous networks – unpacking what they are and what benefits they provide. He also explains how autonomous networks are different from automated networks – and why autonomous networks are superior. Maharaj then discusses whether Africa is ready to adopt autonomous networking before finishing the interview by explaining how businesses can begin their autonomous networking journey with BCX. The full interview with Maharaj can be viewed below. 